&quot;Eric Stanze just won an award for best director at Scare-A-Con for this film. Lives converge in a small town, bringing a trail of blood with them. Frank Logan is looking to find something. Crystal Brewer is looking to escape. The town's people are unaware that their peace is about to be broken, despite some hopes that the past will not catch up to them. There is a remarkable amount of story in this movie for a small budget horror film. Even more interesting: Much of the plot starts after the thirty minute mark. The brutal first half hour feels like a different movie from the second half hour, but it really all does come together in the end. This movie is about as far &quot;Underground&quot; as I've gone with horror in a very long time.&quot;

